# Safety Notice for Serpentine

Effective date: 01/08/2026

Serpentine is designed to help review rides, routes, telemetry, and route performance. It is not a safety system, navigation system, emergency tool, driving assistant, or substitute for your judgment.

By using Serpentine, you are responsible for using the app safely, legally, and appropriately.

## 1. Ride and Drive Safely

Always ride or drive safely and follow all traffic laws, road rules, posted signs, local regulations, and conditions around you.

Do not use Serpentine in a way that distracts you from riding, driving, traffic, pedestrians, road hazards, weather, visibility, or other safety conditions.

Your attention should always remain on the road and your surroundings.

## 2. Do Not Interact With the App While Moving

Do not interact with Serpentine while riding or driving.

Set up your route, device mount, recording mode, permissions, and any app settings before you start moving.

If you need to use the app, change settings, review results, inspect telemetry, import or export data, or interact with the screen, stop in a safe and legal place first.

## 3. Mounting and Device Position

Use a secure device mount if you use Serpentine during a ride or drive.

Make sure the device is mounted in a position that does not block your view, interfere with vehicle controls, distract you, or create a hazard.

You are responsible for making sure your device, mount, charging cable, and any accessories are safe and legal for your vehicle and location.

## 4. Telemetry May Be Inaccurate

Serpentine may show telemetry such as speed, lean angle, G-force, route position, segment timing, route matching, and other ride metrics.

This information may be inaccurate, delayed, incomplete, unavailable, or affected by device sensors, GPS accuracy, mounting position, signal quality, route data, software behavior, battery state, iOS permissions, or environmental conditions.

Do not rely on Serpentine telemetry for real-time safety decisions.

## 5. Not for Navigation or Hazard Detection

Serpentine is not intended to provide navigation, turn-by-turn directions, traffic warnings, hazard detection, collision avoidance, emergency alerts, road condition warnings, or legal advice.

Do not rely on Serpentine to tell you where it is safe to ride or drive.

Do not rely on Serpentine to detect hazards, other vehicles, pedestrians, obstacles, road surface changes, speed limits, police activity, emergency situations, or unsafe conditions.

## 6. Performance Review Only

Serpentine is intended for recording and reviewing ride and route performance.

Use performance data responsibly.

Do not use Serpentine to encourage unsafe riding or driving, excessive speed, illegal racing, reckless behavior, or violations of traffic laws.

Only record performance data in places and circumstances where doing so is safe and legal.

## 7. Background Recording and Automatic Behavior

Serpentine may support features such as background location, automatic route detection, automatic start behavior, automatic finish behavior, or route-based recording.

These features may not start, stop, detect, or record exactly when expected.

You are responsible for confirming that the app is being used safely and appropriately. Do not depend on automatic behavior for safety-critical decisions.

## 8. Routes and Imported Data

Routes, maps, imported files, and route boundaries may contain errors or may not reflect current real-world road conditions.

Roads, routes, access rules, traffic patterns, closures, hazards, and legal restrictions may change.

Always follow real-world signs, laws, and conditions instead of app data.

## 9. Legal Responsibility

You are responsible for complying with all laws and regulations that apply to your riding, driving, device use, data recording, location, vehicle, route, and activity.

Some places may restrict phone use, device mounting, recording, racing, timed driving, or performance measurement. It is your responsibility to know and follow those rules.

## 10. No Emergency Use

Do not use Serpentine as an emergency tool.

If you are in danger, involved in an accident, need medical help, or need emergency assistance, contact local emergency services.

## 11. Assumption of Risk

Riding, driving, motorsport, performance driving, and similar activities involve risk.

You are responsible for your own decisions, your vehicle, your equipment, your device, your route, and your behavior.

Use Serpentine only when it is safe and legal to do so.

